add(2022,13,"Number Theory","The positive difference between a pair of primes is equal to 2, and the positive difference between the cubes of the two primes is 31106. What is the sum of the digits of the least prime that is greater than those two primes?", ["8","10","11","13","16"],"E",S22)
add(2022,14,"Combinatorics","Suppose that S is a subset of {1, 2, 3, ..., 25} such that the sum of any two (not necessarily distinct) elements of S is never an element of S. What is the maximum number of elements S may contain?", ["12","13","14","15","16"],"B",S22)
add(2022,15,"Algebra","Let S_n be the sum of the first n terms of an arithmetic sequence that has a common difference of 2. The quotient S_(3n) / S_n does not depend on n. What is S_20?", ["340","360","380","400","420"],"D",S22)
add(2022,16,"Geometry","The diagram shows a rectangle with side lengths 4 and 8 and a square with side length 5. Three vertices of the square lie on three different sides of the rectangle. What is the area of the region inside both the square and the rectangle?", ["15 1/8","15 3/8","15 1/2","15 5/8","15 7/8"],"D",S22)
add(2022,17,"Number Theory","One of the following numbers is not divisible by any prime number less than 10. Which is it?", ["2^606 - 1","2^606 + 1","2^607 - 1","2^607 + 1","2^607 + 3^607"],"C",S22)
add(2022,18,"Combinatorics","Consider systems of three linear equations with unknowns x, y, and z, where each of the coefficients is either 0 or 1, the constant terms are all 0, and the system has a solution other than x = y = z = 0. How many such systems of equations are there?", ["302","338","340","343","344"],"B",S22)
add(2022,19,"Combinatorics","Each cell of a 5 x 5 grid is either filled or empty. For each cell, the number of filled neighbors (sharing an edge) is counted. A cell becomes filled if it has an odd count, and empty if it has an even count. How many initial configurations will result in a single filled cell at the center after one transformation?", ["14","18","22","26","30"],"C",S22)
add(2022,20,"Geometry","Let ABCD be a rhombus with angle ADC = 46 degrees. Let E be the midpoint of CD, and let F be the point on segment BE such that AF is perpendicular to BE. What is the degree measure of angle BFC?", ["110","111","112","113","114"],"D",S22)
add(2022,21,"Algebra","Let P(x) be a polynomial with rational coefficients such that when P(x) is divided by x^2 + x + 1, the remainder is x + 2, and when P(x) is divided by x^2 + 1, the remainder is 2x + 1. There is a unique polynomial of least degree with these properties. What is the sum of the squares of the coefficients of that polynomial?", ["10","13","19","20","23"],"E",S22)
add(2022,22,"Geometry","Let S be the set of circles in the coordinate plane that are tangent to each of the three circles with equations x^2 + y^2 = 4, x^2 + y^2 = 64, and (x - 5)^2 + y^2 = 3. What is the sum of the areas of all circles in S?", ["48*pi","68*pi","96*pi","102*pi","136*pi"],"E",S22)
add(2022,23,"Probability","Ant Amelia starts on the number line at 0 and crawls in the following manner. For n = 1, 2, 3, Amelia chooses a time duration t_n and an increment x_n independently and uniformly at random from (0, 1). She moves x_n units in the positive direction, using up t_n minutes. If the total elapsed time exceeds 1 minute during the nth step, she stops. Otherwise she continues, taking at most 3 steps. What is the probability that Amelia's final position is greater than 1?", ["1/3","1/2","2/3","3/4","5/6"],"C",S22)
add(2022,24,"Algebra","Consider functions f from the reals to the reals satisfying |f(x) - f(y)| <= (1/2)|x - y| for all real x and y. Of all such functions that also satisfy f(300) = f(900), what is the greatest possible value of f(f(800)) - f(f(400))?", ["25","50","100","150","200"],"B",S22)
add(2022,25,"Number Theory","Let x_0, x_1, x_2, ... be a sequence where each x_k is either 0 or 1. For each positive integer n, define S_n = sum from k=0 to n-1 of x_k * 2^k. Suppose 7 * S_n is congruent to 1 (mod 2^n) for all n >= 1. What is x_2019 + 2*x_2020 + 4*x_2021 + 8*x_2022?", ["6","7","12","14","15"],"A",S22)

S23 = "https://artofproblemsolving.com/wiki/index.php/2023_AMC_10B_Problems"
add(2023,1,"Algebra","Mrs. Jones is pouring orange juice into four identical glasses for her four sons. She fills the first three glasses completely but only fills the fourth glass to 1/3 full. What fraction of a glass must she pour from each of the first three glasses into the fourth glass so that all four glasses will have the same amount of juice?", ["1/12","1/4","1/6","1/8","2/9"],"C",S23)
add(2023,2,"Algebra","Carlos went to a sports store to buy running shoes. Running shoes were on sale, with prices reduced by 20% on every pair of shoes. Carlos also has a coupon that takes an additional 20% off the sale price. He must pay a 7.5% sales tax on the discounted price. He has $43. What is the original (before sales) price of the most expensive pair of running shoes he could afford to buy?", ["$46","$50","$48","$47","$49"],"B",S23)
add(2023,3,"Geometry","A 3-4-5 right triangle is inscribed in circle A, and a 5-12-13 right triangle is inscribed in circle B. What is the ratio of the area of circle A to the area of circle B?", ["9/25","1/9","1/5","25/169","4/25"],"D",S23)
add(2023,4,"Algebra","Jackson's paintbrush makes a strip 6.5 millimeters wide on each stroke. Jackson has enough paint to make a strip 25 meters long. How many square centimeters of area can Jackson paint?", ["162500","162.5","1625","1625000","16250"],"C",S23)
add(2023,5,"Algebra","Madame Irma takes some positive integers on a blackboard and adds 3 to each number. The sum of her new numbers is 45. Lara takes the original numbers and multiplies each by 3. Her sum is also 45. How many numbers are on the blackboard?", ["10","5","6","8","9"],"A",S23)
add(2023,6,"Number Theory","Let L_1 = 1, L_2 = 3, and L_(n+2) = L_(n+1) + L_n for n >= 1. How many terms in the sequence L_1, L_2, ..., L_2023 are even?", ["673","1011","675","1010","674"],"E",S23)
add(2023,7,"Geometry","Square ABCD is rotated 20 degrees clockwise about its center to obtain square EFGH, where E is the image of A. What is the degree measure of angle EAB?", ["24","35","30","32","20"],"B",S23)
add(2023,8,"Number Theory","What is the units digit of 2022^2023 + 2023^2022?", ["7","1","9","5","3"],"A",S23)
add(2023,9,"Number Theory","The numbers 16 and 25 are a pair of consecutive perfect squares whose difference is 9. How many pairs of consecutive perfect squares have a difference that is less than or equal to 2023?", ["674","1011","1010","2019","2017"],"B",S23)
add(2023,10,"Combinatorics","A 2 x 1 rectangle covers two adjacent squares of a 3 x 3 grid of squares, but you are not told which two squares are covered. Your goal is to find at least one square that is covered. On each turn you choose a square and are told whether it is covered or not. What is the minimum number of turns needed to guarantee that at least one covered square is found?", ["3","5","4","8","6"],"C",S23)
add(2023,11,"Combinatorics","Suzanne went to the bank and withdrew $800. The teller gave her this amount using $20 bills, $50 bills, and $100 bills, with at least one of each denomination. How many different combinations of bills could the teller have given Suzanne?", ["45","21","36","28","32"],"B",S23)
add(2023,12,"Algebra","When the roots of the polynomial P(x) = (x - 1)^1 * (x - 2)^2 * (x - 3)^3 * ... * (x - 10)^10 are removed from the number line, what remains is the union of 11 disjoint open intervals. On how many of these intervals is P(x) > 0?", ["3","7","6","4","5"],"C",S23)
add(2023,13,"Algebra","What is the area of the region in the coordinate plane defined by ||x| - 1| + ||y| - 1| <= 1?", ["2","8","4","15","12"],"B",S23)
add(2023,14,"Algebra","How many ordered pairs of integers (m, n) satisfy the equation m^2 + mn + n^2 = m^2 * n^2?", ["7","1","3","6","5"],"C",S23)
add(2023,15,"Number Theory","What is the least positive integer m such that m * 2! * 3! * 4! * 5! * ... * 16! is a perfect square?", ["30","30030","70","1430","1001"],"C",S23)
add(2023,16,"Combinatorics","Define a positive integer n to be an 'upno' if every pair of consecutive digits of n, read left to right, is strictly increasing, and define a positive integer to be a 'downno' if every pair of consecutive digits, read left to right, is strictly decreasing. Let U equal the total number of upnos and D equal the total number of downnos. What is |U - D|?", ["512","10","0","9","511"],"E",S23)
add(2023,17,"Algebra","A rectangular box P has distinct edge lengths a, b, and c. The sum of the lengths of all 12 edges of P is 13, the sum of the areas of all 6 faces of P is 11/2, and the volume of P is 1/2. What is the length of the longest interior diagonal of P?", ["2","3/8","9/8","9/4","3/2"],"D",S23)
add(2023,18,"Number Theory","Suppose a/14 + b/15 = c/210, where a, b, and c are positive integers. Consider: I. If gcd(a,14)=1 or gcd(b,15)=1, then gcd(c,210)=1. II. If gcd(c,210)=1, then gcd(a,14)=1 or gcd(b,15)=1. III. gcd(c,210)=1 if and only if gcd(a,14)=gcd(b,15)=1. Which are true?", ["I, II, and III","I only","I and II only","III only","II and III only"],"E",S23)
add(2023,19,"Probability","Sonya the frog randomly chooses a landing point uniformly in [0,6] x [0,6] and hops there. She then randomly chooses a distance from [0,1] and one of four directions (north, south, east, west) each with probability 1/4. What is the probability she lands outside the square after the second hop?", ["1/6","1/12","1/4","1/10","1/9"],"B",S23)
add(2023,20,"Geometry","Four congruent semicircles are drawn on the surface of a sphere of radius 2. Each semicircle has its diameter as a diameter of the sphere, and the endpoints of all diameters are the same two points. The four semicircular arcs divide the surface into two congruent regions. The length of the curve is pi * sqrt(n). What is n?", ["32","12","48","36","27"],"A",S23)
add(2023,21,"Probability","Each of 2023 balls is randomly placed into one of 3 bins. Which of the following is closest to the probability that each of the three bins will contain an odd number of balls?", ["2/3","3/10","1/2","1/3","1/4"],"E",S23)
add(2023,22,"Algebra","How many distinct values of x satisfy floor(x)^2 - 3x + 2 = 0, where floor(x) denotes the greatest integer not exceeding x?", ["an infinite number","4","2","3","0"],"B",S23)
add(2023,23,"Number Theory","An arithmetic sequence of positive integers has n >= 3 terms, initial term a, and common difference d > 1. Carl found the sum of all terms but inadvertently wrote one term incorrectly, off by 1. The incorrect sum was 222. How many possible values are there for a + d + n?", ["24","20","22","28","26"],"B",S23)
add(2023,24,"Geometry","What is the perimeter of the boundary of the region consisting of all points which can be expressed as (2u - 3w, v + 4w) with 0 <= u <= 1, 0 <= v <= 1, 0 <= w <= 1?", ["10*sqrt(3)","13","12","18","16"],"E",S23)
add(2023,25,"Geometry","A regular pentagon with area 1 + sqrt(5) is printed on paper and cut out. All five vertices are folded to the center, creating a smaller pentagon. What is the area of the new smaller pentagon?", ["4 - sqrt(5)","sqrt(5) - 1","8 - 3*sqrt(5)","(sqrt(5) + 1)/2","(2 + sqrt(5))/3"],"B",S23)

S25 = "https://artofproblemsolving.com/wiki/index.php/2025_AMC_10B_Problems"
add(2025,1,"Algebra","A 350-gram bag of coffee beans requires 20 grams of beans per large mug of coffee. What is the greatest number of large mugs of coffee that can be brewed from one bag?", ["16","17","18","19","20"],"B",S25)
add(2025,2,"Number Theory","Jerry wrote down the ones digit of each of the first 2025 positive perfect squares: 1, 4, 9, 6, 5, 6, 9, 4, 1, 0, ... What is the sum of all the digits Jerry wrote down?", ["9025","9070","9090","9115","9160"],"D",S25)
add(2025,3,"Algebra","A triangle whose rows begin and end with special values: the first row is 10, the second row is 10 and 1, and each subsequent row starts with 10, ends with 1, and each interior entry is the sum of the two entries directly above it. What is the sum of the digits of the sum of the numbers in the 11th row?", ["11","13","14","16","17"],"D",S25)
add(2025,4,"Number Theory","The two-digit number ab in base 7 has the same value as the two-digit number ba in base 9. What is a + b?", ["7","9","10","11","14"],"A",S25)
add(2025,5,"Geometry","In triangle ABC, AB = 10, AC = 18, and angle B = 130 degrees. Let O be the center of the circumscribed circle. What is the degree measure of angle CAO?", ["20","30","40","50","60"],"C",S25)
add(2025,6,"Geometry","The line y = (1/3)x + 1 divides the square region 0 <= x <= 2, 0 <= y <= 2 into an upper region and a lower region. The vertical line x = a further divides the lower region into two regions of equal area. Then a can be written in the form sqrt(s) - t, where s and t are positive integers. What is s + t?", ["18","19","20","21","22"],"C",S25)
add(2025,7,"Algebra","Frances is standing 15 meters due south of a locked gate. A box of chocolates is x meters due east of the locked gate. An unlocked gate is 9 meters due east of the box, and a second unlocked gate is 8 meters due west of the locked gate. The total distance walked via either unlocked gate to reach the box is the same. What is x?", ["3 2/7","3 3/7","3 4/7","3 5/7","3 6/7"],"C",S25)
add(2025,8,"Algebra","Emmy ordered 36 custom sweatshirts for her club. The total cost was $ABB.BA, where A and B represent digits and A is not 0. What is A + B?", ["7","8","11","14","15"],"C",S25)
add(2025,9,"Algebra","How many ordered triples of integers (x, y, z) satisfy the system: -x - y - z <= -2, -x + y + z <= 2, x - y + z <= 2, and x + y - z <= 2?", ["4","8","11","15","17"],"C",S25)
add(2025,10,"Algebra","Let f(n) = n^3 - 5n^2 + 2n + 8 and g(n) = n^3 - 6n^2 + 5n + 12. What is the sum of all integers n such that f(n)/g(n) is defined and is an integer?", ["2","3","4","5","6"],"A",S25)
add(2025,11,"Probability","On Monday, 6 students were each randomly assigned to one of 6 tutors, one student per tutor. On Tuesday, the same 6 students and 6 tutors were present, and students were again randomly assigned one per tutor. What is the probability that exactly 2 of the 6 students had the same tutor on both days?", ["1/16","3/16","1/4","3/8","1/2"],"B",S25)
add(2025,12,"Geometry","An equilateral triangle, a rhombus with 60-degree angles, and a regular hexagon each contain the maximum number of mutually tangent nonoverlapping congruent circular disks. Let T, R, and H denote the ratio of total disk area to polygon area for each. Which is true?", ["T = H = R","H < R = T","H = R < T","H < R < T","H < T < R"],"C",S25)
add(2025,13,"Geometry","In a right triangle with angles 30, 60, and 90 degrees, the altitude to the hypotenuse has length h. The median to the shortest side divides the altitude into two segments of lengths x and y, where x < y. What is x/(x + y)?", ["3/7","sqrt(3)/4","4/9","5/11","4*sqrt(3)/15"],"A",S25)
add(2025,14,"Probability","Nine athletes with distinct heights draw wristbands from a bag containing 3 blue, 3 red, and 3 green wristbands. The tallest athlete with each color band becomes that team's captain. What is the probability that the three tallest athletes overall are the three captains?", ["2/9","2/7","9/28","1/3","3/8"],"C",S25)
add(2025,15,"Algebra","The sum from k = 1 to infinity of 1/(k^3 + 6k^2 + 8k) can be expressed as a/b, where a and b are relatively prime positive integers. What is a + b?", ["89","97","102","107","129"],"D",S25)
add(2025,16,"Combinatorics","A circle is divided into 6 equal sectors by 3 diameters. The sectors are painted, two red, two green, and two blue, such that no two adjacent sectors are the same color. How many distinct colorings are possible?", ["12","16","18","24","28"],"D",S25)
add(2025,17,"Algebra","A strictly decreasing sequence of n positive integers x_1 > x_2 > ... > x_n has the property that the average of the first 3 terms equals 2025, and for each 4 <= k <= n, the average of the first k terms is 1 less than the average of the first k - 1 terms. What is the greatest possible value of n?", ["1013","1014","1016","2016","2025"],"B",S25)
add(2025,18,"Number Theory","What is the ones digit of floor(sqrt(1)) + floor(sqrt(2)) + ... + floor(sqrt(2025))?", ["1","2","3","5","8"],"D",S25)
add(2025,19,"Geometry","A container has a bottom that is a 1 x 1 square and an open top that is a 3 x 3 square. The four sides are congruent trapezoids. Water from a hose fills the container to the midline in 35 minutes. How many more minutes does it take to fill the rest?", ["70","85","90","95","105"],"D",S25)
add(2025,20,"Geometry","Four congruent semicircles are inscribed in a unit square, each with diameter on one of the four sides. One endpoint of each diameter is a vertex of the square, and adjacent semicircles are tangent to each other. A small circle at the center of the square is tangent to all four semicircles. The diameter of the small circle can be written as (sqrt(a) + b)(sqrt(c) + d). What is a + b + c + d?", ["3","5","8","9","11"],"A",S25)
add(2025,21,"Combinatorics","Each unit square in a 3 x 3 grid is colored red, blue, or yellow so that each red square shares an edge with at least one blue square, each blue square shares an edge with at least one yellow square, and each yellow square shares an edge with at least one red square. How many such colorings are there, counting rotations and reflections of the same coloring only once?", ["3","9","12","18","27"],"C",S25)
add(2025,22,"Number Theory","A seven-digit positive integer n is chosen at random. What is the probability that n is divisible by 11, given that the sum of its digits is 61?", ["3/14","3/11","2/7","4/11","3/7"],"A",S25)
add(2025,23,"Number Theory","Horace and Vera each fill a 141 x 91 grid with integers 1 through 12831. Horace fills row by row (left to right, top to bottom). Vera fills column by column (top to bottom, left to right). How many squares receive the same number from both?", ["7","10","11","12","19"],"C",S25)
add(2025,24,"Probability","A frog starts at position 0. From 0, it moves to 1 with probability 1/2 or disappears with probability 1/2. From any position n >= 1, it moves to n+1 with probability 1/4, to n-1 with probability 1/4, or disappears with probability 1/2. What is the probability it reaches position 4?", ["1/101","1/100","1/99","1/98","1/97"],"E",S25)
add(2025,25,"Geometry","Square ABCD has side length 4. Point P lies on side AD with AP = 8/5, and point Q lies on side CD with DQ = 10/3. A light beam is shot from P toward Q. When the beam hits a side, it reflects with equal angles of incidence and reflection. At which vertex does the beam eventually terminate?", ["A","B","C","D","The path never terminates"],"B",S25)

